Use the standard library
This is how to sorted_list_sum of lst:
  Remember that groups is {}
  Remember that result is []
  Do this lst's length times:
    Remember that i is diff of lst's length and 1
    Remember that i is diff of i and result's length
    Remember that x is item i in lst
    Remember that n is x's length
    When n is in groups, then:
      Add item n in groups to result
      Leave the loop
    End when
    Remember that item n in groups is x
  End do
  The answer is result
